The '''1987 [[Libyan Premier League]]''' was the 19th edition of the competition since its inception in 1963. The league consisted of 18 teams, who played each other just once. The first round of matches were played on March 20, 1987, and the final round of games were played on August 28, 1987. [[Benghazi]] club [[Nasr Benghazi|Nasr]] won their first title (and to date, their only one) by one point, from [[Almadina S.C.|Madina]].
